parameters:
\n<Radro>Yes, yes! If you dig a hole, make sure to fill it back in!
We can't have someone falling and getting hurt, right?

\n<Radro>Aventus is a child who recently arrived, and it seems like
their emotional wounds haven't healed yet.

\n<Radro>The feelings of a child abandoned by their parents... I've
been there myself, but I wonder how I can save them.

\n<Radro>Do you think it's strange to run an orphanage in a place
like this? It's precisely because it's this kind of place
that it's needed. Maybe it's still a difficult topic for
\n[1]?

\n<Radro>There are so many tough things to deal with, but when I see
the children's energetic faces, all those troubles seem to
fade away.

\n<Radro>It's not the time to be tired. Realizing that there are
things only I can do makes me feel happy.

\n<Radro>This town, Dri-Ne, is called a "dumping ground." People
living above throw away things they no longer need here.

\n<Radro>To them, we might just be "ants swarming over spilled ice
cream." In reality, we sometimes wait for usable things to
fall from above.

\n<Radro>I wonder what kind of adults these children will become. The
public order is bad, it's dirty, and I can't provide them
with a proper education, but still, I have hope for them.

\n<Radro>I was taught a lot of kindness by "Mama." So, even in a
place like this, no matter how dirty it gets, I want to pass
that on to these children.

\n<Radro>Hey hey, cat beastfolk are so cute♥ I wish I had ears like
that. And a tail would be nice too. Can I touch it?

\n<Radro>I won't pry if you don't want me to, but you come from a
prestigious family, right? Are you really okay with being in
a place like this?

\n<Radro>If you have a place to return to, you should go back
properly, you know? Well, I'm sure there are various
circumstances so I won't say anything more.

\n<Radro>The other day, trash falling from above almost hit a child
and I just snapped! I went up there to complain!

\n<Radro>Then I was sincerely apologized to and even given money...
They were really nice people, and somehow, I couldn't stay
mad at them.

\n<Radro>Maybe the one who was discriminating based on where we live
was me after all.

\n<Radro>It's a town with bad public order and lots of drunkards and
criminals, but when it comes to the orphanage, everyone is
kind. It's because the previous "Mama" was such a wonderful
person.

\n<Radro>Mama was quite the drinker too. In the end, she died due to
liver problems. But still, I will carry on her will.

\n<Samuel>Dig dig dig... If I dig a hole here, some really gross bugs
come out. I'll show them to you when they do.

\n<Constance>Radro is so good at cooking! She praises me a lot if I
eat everything without leaving any, but I can't leave any
even if I wanted to! Because it's delicious!

\n<Constance>But then, Samuel starts mocking me saying "You'll get fat,"
and it always turns into a fight. I don't even want to
fight!

parameters.name: 探索15(セキュリティホール)

parameters:
\n<Wanzworth>So, let's call it a draw...! *pant*...*sigh*... We should be
safe for a while if we've come this far, right?

\n<Wanzworth>Ew... This town isn't very pretty, is it. (It smells a bit
strange...)

\n<Louiesham>Mmm... It looks like there's an adventurers' guild and an
inn.
\n<Wanzworth>It might be a good place to hide. It stinks though.
\n<Louiesham>For now, let's just do what we can.
